  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ethiopia Humanitarian Fund (EHF).The EHF is a UN-OCHA managed multi-donor fund which provides grants to UN agencies and NGOs for the delivery of immediate life-saving humanitarian assistance. The objectives of the EHF are aligned with supporting the humanitarian reform agenda in Ethiopia. In 2020, the EHF provided life-saving support (emergency non-food assistance) through the Humanitarian Response Plan (HRP) which aims to reach 7 million out of the 8.4 million people identified as in need of humanitarian assistance, of which 73 per cent have acute humanitarian needs that must be addressed immediately.</narrative>
  </description>
